\ array ( v1 ... vN n -- arr ) — gather the top N stack items into an
\ array, preserving order and duplicates.

\ basic gather
1 2 3 3 array .                      \ [ 1 2 3 ]

\ order is preserved (unlike set)
10 20 30 3 array .                   \ [ 10 20 30 ]

\ duplicates are kept (unlike set)
5 5 5 3 array .                      \ [ 5 5 5 ]

\ mixed types
"a" 42 "b" 3 array .                 \ [ a 42 b ]

\ empty array
0 array .                            \ [ ]

\ gather leaves items below the count alone
99 1 2 3 3 array . . cr              \ [ 1 2 3 ] 99

\ length via size
1 2 3 4 5 5 array size .      \ 5

\ round-trip through @i
7 8 9 3 array 1 @i .                 \ 8
